    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential crash in scheduling_request_config due to missing validation\n\n### Summary\nThe `scheduling_request_config()` function in the NR MAC gNB code could crash when called with PUCCH configurations that lack resource sets or resources. The function assumed the existence of resource set 0 and its resources without proper validation, leading to null pointer dereferences.\n\nThis fix adds validation checks to prevent crashes when PUCCH resource sets or resources are not available. The function now logs appropriate error messages and returns gracefully when the required resources are missing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/nr_radio_config.c`: Added validation checks in `scheduling_request_config()` to verify the existence of PUCCH resource sets and resources before accessing them.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure a UE with a PUCCH configuration that has no resource sets\n2. Call `scheduling_request_config()` with this configuration\n3. The function would crash with a segmentation fault due to null pointer dereference\n\nAfter this fix, the function will log an error message and return without crashing.\n"
}